[normal]Q229 [bold]&#xa0; 
[normal]Siobhain [bold]McDonagh[bold]:[bold] Written evidence to the inquiry includes a suggestion that the central admissions portal for apprenticeships, modelled on UCAS for higher education, could make it easier for young people to find out about and enrol for apprenticeships.  Do you agree?  Would this be particularly helpful for working class students who may not have the same social capital as their middle class peers applying for degrees?
[normal]Conor[bold] Ryan[bold]: Anything that makes the system more navigable and easier for students and for teachers to see what is available in terms of apprenticeships would be a good thing.
[normal]Keith Smith[bold]: It would be a mistake to not recognise there is already a national apprenticeship vacancy system, where pretty much every apprenticeship vacancy that is offered is advertised.  Young people and adults alike can download an 
[normal]iPhone
[normal] app where you can search on your 
[normal]smartphone
[normal] the apprenticeship vacancies by sector, job, location, etc.  
[normal]&#xa0;
