[normal]Owen Jones[bold]: Just to go back to family breakdown quickly, the Children’s Society have looked into this in great detail, and their findings were that conflict within families has 10 times more of an impact on a child’s development than the family structure.  The point you have made about the underlying issue being poverty—single parents are far more likely to live in poverty, and that is something that you cannot separate.  All the evidence shows, for 
[normal]example, middle class students do well whatever school they go to.  There was one study in 2008 that found that middle class kids at inner
[normal]-
