[normal]Owen Jones[bold]: When we talk about odds being stacked against people, if it is 10 to one, then obviously 10% of people will overcome that particular obstacle.  When we are looking at housing, overcrowding simply means lack of places for people to study.  Some people get around that; it just means you have a far greater obstacle to overcome.  The wider point about homework again comes back to cultural capital.  If you have parents who themselves are professional middle class university-educated people, then they are in a far better position to be able to help with homework.  
